During a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Sarah Sanders previewed President Trump's plans for the rest of the week, including his visit to H&K Equipment company in Pennsylvania and his address to the March for Life from the White House. Sanders also introduced Ed O'Callaghan from the Department of Justice, who discussed the Section 11 report on international terrorism-related offenses. O'Callaghan highlighted the urgent need for Congress to adopt immigration reforms and provided statistics on terrorism-related convictions and removals. Sanders later fielded questions on topics such as executive privilege, the government shutdown, and Steve Bannon's testimony in the Russia investigation.